# Read the CSV file into a data frame named 'spfyt'

spfyt = read_csv("datasets/Spotify_Youtube.csv")


# Data cleaning: Convert 'Channel' to a factor with the top 50 most
# frequent levels Calculate the frequency of each level in 'Channel'

channel_freq <- table(spfyt$Channel)

# Select the top 50 levels based on frequency

top50_levels <- names(sort(channel_freq, decreasing = TRUE)[1:50])

# Convert 'Channel' to a factor with the selected levels

spfyt$Channel <- factor(spfyt$Channel, levels = top50_levels)

# Convert 'Licensed' to a factor

spfyt$Licensed <- as.factor(spfyt$Licensed)

# Remove rows with missing values

spfyt <- na.omit(spfyt)

# Build a random forest classification model named 'randomforest111'

randomforest111 <- randomForest(Likes ~ Danceability + Duration_ms + Channel +
    Licensed, data = spfyt, type = "classification", mtry = 3, na.action = na.roughfix,
    ntree = 150, importance = TRUE)



# Plot the variable importance of the random forest model

varImpPlot(randomforest111)



# Create a partial dependence plot for 'Danceability' in the context
# of 'randomforest111'

pdp::partial(randomforest111, pred.var = "Danceability", plot = TRUE, rug = TRUE,
    plot.engine = "ggplot2", smooth = TRUE, trim.outliers = FALSE, prob = TRUE,
    center = TRUE, type = "regression", which.class = 2)
